something spontaneous for a change, and…

37:50.851 --> 37:53.312
[nervously] …I thought
it would be romantic.

37:55.481 --> 37:56.482
What's wrong?

37:58.526 --> 37:59.819
Mel, I, um…

38:02.071 --> 38:07.368
I met with an attorney today
about custody of the twins.

38:08.786 --> 38:10.037
Oh. [sighs]

38:10.121 --> 38:12.331
-[Mel] How did that go?
-Not great.

38:14.250 --> 38:15.584
If I wanna be in their lives,

38:15.668 --> 38:18.087
I'm facing
a long and expensive court battle.

38:19.005 --> 38:20.131
[quietly] Oh.

38:20.214 --> 38:21.590
I'm so sorry.

38:22.842 --> 38:25.845
[Mel] You know that I support you
whatever you need to do.

38:27.888 --> 38:29.348
I know, um…

38:30.182 --> 38:31.350
It's just…

38:34.645 --> 38:36.564
Uh, I feel like…

38:37.815 --> 38:39.400
[groans]

38:39.900 --> 38:42.361
…you're gonna get
the short end of the stick.

38:42.445 --> 38:45.531
I don't understand what that means.
Are you talking about money?

38:45.614 --> 38:48.868
-I don't care about money.
-No, it's not just money.

38:48.951 --> 38:50.202
It's time too.

38:50.786 --> 38:52.872
Mel, for the next year, at least,

38:52.955 --> 38:55.082
I'm gonna be juggling being a new father,

38:55.166 --> 38:56.584
